</p>
<p class="para">“Go home. You’re in the way.”</p>
<p class="para">No matter how harshly he turned her away, Furiae only shook her head, firm and unmoving.</p>
<p class="para">“Inuart is worried about you.”</p>
<p class="para">“He doesn’t have to be. I told him I was coming.”</p>
<p class="para">“It’s not just about whether you told him or not.”</p>
<p class="para">“Yes, it is.”</p>
<p class="para">Furiae lowered her gaze.</p>
<p class="para">“I can’t stay by his side…Not when I feel like this.”</p>
<p class="para">Caim realized then: it wasn’t just him. She too had been tormented by the countless rumors—truths and lies twisted together. </p>
<p class="para">He sighed and looked up at the sky.</p>
<p class="para">“Do as you like.”</p>
<p class="para">The sky was a clear, piercing blue. Winter was close now.
    <br>But when he cast his eyes back to the ground, all he saw was scorched earth stretching on and on.
    <br>A line of people trudged past, heads bowed beneath the weight of small bundles strapped to their backs.
