</p>
<p class="para">“It… hurts… Brother…”</p>
<p class="para">Furiae’s face twisted in pain. Sweat streamed down her cold forehead. The image from earlier that day flashed through Caim’s mind—the black flag raised over the sanctuary. He’d heard before: when a new candidate is chosen, a spiral-shaped script appears on the goddess’s body to mark her. This spiral-shaped light—could it be?</p>
<p class="para">No. This is an illness.</p>
<p class="para">He laid Furiae’s body gently on the bed, then burst out of the room. The innkeeper, startled by the commotion, was already getting up.</p>
<p class="para">“Get a healer! She’s sick!”</p>
<p class="para">But the one who came was not a healer—it was a priest from the sanctuary. The innkeeper, who had opened the shutters to summon help, froze in place. Slowly, with a look of pity, he turned to face Caim.</p>
<p class="para">A black flag raised. A priest arriving. No one could mistake what that meant.</p>
<p class="para">“By order of the High Priest, I’ve come to escort her.”</p>
