</p>
<p class="para">“Even so—I’ll survive!”</p>
<p class="para">Fueled by rage, he charged.
    <br>It made him furious. Of all times, they had to interrupt this?
</p>
<p class="para">“Out of my way!”</p>
<p class="para">He struck with his sword, but the fury didn’t fade. His whole body was burning.
    <br>Was the red in his vision from the blood splattered across his face—or from the fury boiling in his veins?</p>
<p class="para">Come on.
    <br>I’ll kill every last one of you!
</p>
<p class="para">Where was this anger coming from?
    <br>Was it because they interrupted the pact?
