    <br>I…
</p>
<p class="para">“You survived?”</p>
<p class="para">The dragon’s voice came from behind him.
    <br>Before he realized it, the corpses of the Imperial soldiers lay scattered across the ground.
</p>
<p class="para">“You’re a lucky one.”</p>
<p class="para">Its voice had a hint of laughter to it, but its breath was even more ragged than before.
    <br>It was dying.
    <br>There wasn’t a moment left to lose.
</p>
<p class="para">Caim turned around.
    <br>The earth lurched beneath him.
    <br>He caught himself with his sword like a cane. Pain shot through him.
</p>
<p class="para">“Your answer…”</p>
<p class="para">Each breath felt like a hand tightening around his spine.
    <br>He didn’t have much time left either.
</p>
<p class="para">“A pact? Or death?”</p>
<p class="para">His vision blurred.
    <br>Even his own voice sounded distant.
    <br>Stumbling, legs trembling, he moved toward the dragon.
</p>
<p class="para">It still lay with its head to the ground, but slowly, it opened its eyes.</p>
<p class="para">“I swear on your will to live.”</p>
